  "elapsed_s": 6.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Stephen Muller.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "S-T-E-P-H-E-N M-U- double L-E-R.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Poland, I was called Stefan, S-T-E-F-A-N, Muller but with an umlaut on the u, the two dots on the u, which is a German version of-- of the name.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Shlomo.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "22Nd of May, 1936.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "59.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was born in a little village called Bochnia in Poland.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it's rather vague in my mind, but I do remember several things about it.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was-- I remember the village itself, and that was also reinforced when I came to see it again later on in my life.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was a sort of small-- smallish, rural type of Polish-- typical Polish town.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We had a fairly large home, I think, with a very large kitchen.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The reason why I remember the kitchen is that I ran along the polished floor, not too dissimilar to what we have here in this house, as a young child and I slipped.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I bashed myself in the corner of a chair, just above my right eye.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And if I had-- if I had done that just a little bit below, I would be now speaking with one blind eye.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So that's a memory-- the first traumatic memory that I have.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And sort of the surroundings of the place that I lived in.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I remember one bedroom because I was sick one day.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And in those days, the doctor used to come, and was, of course, before the antibiotic era, or before any type of medication, really.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they used to put these very hot, glass-- like glasses, on top-- on your back.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that was supposed to draw out the inflammation from your lungs.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
